nit about needing metadata for fields and methods related to `sun.misc.Unsafe`, DummyOne/Two, and Long fields for native scenarios. It seems like there shouldn't be an issue if classes initialize at build time, but runtime raises concerns. Should I add reachability metadata? Only the test resource can register library classes for native tests. Yet, users need the `RamUsageEstimator` to function properly under native conditions. I wonder if we need to generate metadata for dynamic access class tests, considering the user mainly wants tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test resource usage**\\n\\nI’m considering that test resources are generally meant for user-provided application metadata, which seems acceptable. But should tests also prove that the library works with this metadata? The repository metadata ideally should consist of actual metadata rather than test resources, unless it's user code. However, test classes will need reflection configuration, and that can't be incorporated into the library metadata. It feels like I’m navigating a complex boundary here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_v0lUYH5gSlqaDVnTeOpsbqXu|fc_0f30fef217396aea0169f615be0a2081a284969db6d46583fc", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/4.10.4/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/ram-usage-estimator-test/reflect-config.json", "content": "[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"sun.misc.Unsafe\",\n    \"allDeclaredFields\": true,\n    \"allPublicMethods\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"com.sun.management.HotSpotDiagnosticMXBean\",\n    \"allPublicMethods\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"com.sun.management.VMOption\",\n    \"allPublicMethods\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"java.lang.Long\",\n    \"allDeclaredFields\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"java.lang.Number\",\n    \"allDeclaredFields\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"java.lang.Object\",\n    \"allDeclaredFields\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"org.apache.